In separate small bowls or combined in a large bowl, gently mix the fresh fruit with sugar and lemon juice to taste. In a deep bowl, with a mixer on high speed, beat whipping cream until it holds soft peaks. Fold in yogurt and add honey to taste. Mound in a bowl and drizzle more honey decoratively over the top. Set cake on platter. For each portion, cut a 3/4-inch slice and transfer to a plate. Spoon fruit and accumulated juices over cake, and top with yogurt-cream mixture.